vastated buildings in the background, but this time the image showed a pair of <small>;IDF</small>; troops chatting in the foreground.它捕获了一个重要的观点。在耶路撒冷或特拉维夫并不总是承认以色列的黯淡前景。许多以色列人认为，对其国家的独特威胁证明了其残酷的理由，战争有助于恢复威慑。 Many see no partner for peace—the <small>;PA</small>; is rotten and polls say 93% of Palestinians deny Hamas's atrocities even took place. Occupation is the least-bad option, they conclude. Israelis would prefer to be popular abroad, but condemnation and antisemitism are a small price to pay for security.<br>;<br>;Our choice was an eloquent riposte to that line of thinking.一个苗条的分支支撑的以色列国旗被风燃烧，并靠在加沙的废墟上。 Israel faces a long-term threat from Iran and its proxies, including Hizbullah.阻止这种情况需要与美国需要两党支持的军事伙伴关系，理想情况下也需要阿拉伯海湾支持。经济取决于技术出口和进入全球市场的专家。 And rather than making Israelis safe, permanent occupation poisons politics by emboldening the hard right and breeding Palestinian radicalism. Israelis are right that they have no partner for peace today, but they are best placed to break the cycle. <br>;<br>;A struggle for Israel's future awaits. The battle in Gaza is just the start.</p>;<div class="css-0 e18kpe850">;<style data-emotion="css 1xcoyz7">;.css-1xcoyz7 img{display:block;}.css-1xcoyz7 .e1sa5x7b2{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style>;<figure class="css-1xcoyz7 e1197rjj0">;<img loading="lazy" width="1280" height="1709" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 834px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20240323_DE_US.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20240323_DE_US.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20240323_DE_US.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20240323_DE_US.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-